cff-version: 1.2.0
title: >-
  BrandDocs - turn a company's Word, PowerPoint or Excel
  template into unlimited on-brand documents
message: >-
  If you use this software, please cite it using the
  metadata from this file.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Ferdinando
    family-names: Bonsegna
repository-code: 'https://github.com/ferdinandobons/brand-docs'
url: 'https://github.com/ferdinandobons/brand-docs'
abstract: >-
  BrandDocs is an open-source agent-skill bundle for Claude Code, Codex and
  compatible AI agents. It extracts a company's Office template (.docx, .pptx,
  .xlsx) into a reusable Brand Profile, then generates new on-brand documents
  from the original template shell. Off-brand output is impossible by
  construction: generators never write literal style names, colors or fonts,
  and verification fails on any artifact the template does not define.
keywords:
  - claude-code
  - claude-skill
  - ai-agents
  - brand-identity
  - document-generation
  - docx
  - pptx
  - xlsx
  - ooxml
  - office-automation
  - python-docx
  - python-pptx
  - openpyxl
license: MIT
version: 0.9.0
date-released: '2026-06-10'
